rison Co  West Virginia  and died 24 September 1911 in Buckhannon  Upshur Co  WV  buried Heavner Cemetery  Upshur Co  She married JONATHAN ARNOLD 01 September 1844  they were divorced in 1870  He was born 27 March 1802 in West Brownsville  Fayette Co  PA  and died 20 July 1883 in Beverly  Randolph Co  WV  Children of LAURA JACKSON and JONATHAN ARNOLD are  2  i  THOMAS JACKSON ARNOLD  b  03 November 1845  Beverly  Randolph Co  WV  d  10 January 1933  Arnold Hill  Beverly  Randolph Co  WV  3  ii  ANNA GRACE ARNOLD  b  23 March 1848  Beverly  Randolph Co  WV  d  18 March 1878  Cincinnati  OH  4  iii  STARK WILLIAM ARNOLD  b  02 December 1851  Beverly  Randolph Co  WV  d  16 August 1898  Ocean Grove  NJ  iv  LAURA ZELL ARNOLD  b  19 December 1853  d  May 1854  Generation No  2  2  THOMAS JACKSON ARNOLD was born 03 November 1845 in Beverly  Randolph Co  WV  and died 10 January 1933 in Arnold Hill  Beverly  Randolph Co  WV  He married MARY EUGENIA HILL 01 June 1876  daughter of DANIEL HILL and ISABELLA MORRISON  She was born 29 April 1852 in Lexington  Virginia  and died 24 November 1934 in Arnold Hill  Beverly  Randolph Co  WV  MARY S mother  ISABELLA  was the sister of Mary Anna Morrison  second wife of Thomas Jonathan  Stonewall  Jackson  her husband s uncle and namesake  Children of THOMAS ARNOLD and MARY HILL are  i  ISABELLA ARNOLD  b  1877  ii  DANIEL HARVEY HILL ARNOLD  b 1879  iii  THOMAS JACKSON ARNOLD  JR  b  1883  iv  EUGENE HILL ARNOLD  b  1890  3  ANNA GRACE ARNOLD was born 23 March 1848 in Beverly  Randolph Co  WV  and died 18 March 1878 in Cincinnati  OH  buried Springfield  OH  She married MAJ  CHARLES H  EVANS 12 December 1866  Children of ANNA ARNOLD and CHARLES EVANS are  i  HOWARD STARK EVANS  1871 1874  ii  CHARLES  CHARLEY  THOMAS EVANS  1873 1874  4  STARK WILLIAM ARNOLD was born 02 December 1851 in Beverly  Randolph Co  WV  and died 16 August 1898 in Ocean Grove  NJ  He married ELIZABETH ELLEN GOHEN Bet  25 December 1880 or 1881  She was born 10 January 1851  and died 30 June 1918  Children of STARK ARNOLD and ELIZABETH GOHEN are  i  GRACE DECOURCEY ARNOLD  b  1881  ii  MARIE ESTELLE ARNOLD  b  1883  iii  GOHEN CLARK ARNOLD  b  1885  iv  BEATRICE SOUVENIR ARNOLD  b  1887  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 